To remove the dynamic detection you need to change the behavior of the program which gives this detection, for example if the program goes into the registry and writes there, the antivirus notices it. To prevent it from noticing, you have to change the behavior, for example, to make another program, such as BITS, look in the registry and write there.

To remove the static detector, you need to find a place in the program code, which gives this detector and change it (for example, add some trash code, swap lines in the code, the order of function calls, etc.). But this does not change the behavior of the program itself.
